<br>
I just started a monk for the first time, got him to 20 yesterday &amp; trained the skills. Now, I see monks not in combat doing kicks &amp; punches at the air all the time, and I know they're practicing their skills... which is what my monk needs to do, since I PL'd him to 20 on my second account to have a partner for my 22 shammie when I feel like being self-sufficient.<br>
<br>
But how do you do it? Do you just target yourself and hit the button, or does it work with no target selected?<br>
<br>
I'll try it when I get home, but would appreciate advice to save me time fumbling around. Thanks! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/udaleb123.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Daleb123</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Monk</span><br>  Posts: 173<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(7/13/02 3:27:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1697.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Instill Doubt</span><hr size=1> What you are seeing is Monks practicing the Instill Doubt skill. Target anything, and press your Instill Doubt hot key (make one, if you haven't already).<br>
<br>
Note that a successful ID skill check will result in a kick if you are in melee range of your target (and it is a legal attack target); if the kick lands, this acts as a fear spell on your opponent. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/udaithi2.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Daithi2</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 15<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(7/14/02 7:26:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1697.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://images.art.com/images/products/shdws/small/10053000/10053867.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Instill Doubt</span><hr size=1> unless they resist... then ya done pissed em off just practice it when you have free time when skill is up you get less resists and more chances to instill fear <p>Daithii Lightingdragon - 54 Iksar monky- 
